OL,3,CDad who lost son in car park fall
OL,4,C'confident' the Government is listening
OL,6,FHe said he is calling for a change in
OL,7,Fthe law because "the parking industry
OL,8,Faren't responding in the responsible
OL,9,Fand moral way that they should be.
OL,11,F"They are currently only doing what
OL,12,Fthe legislation actually calls for in
OL,13,Fterms of minimum requirements, and as
OL,14,Fwe know from countless times, this is
OL,15,Fjust simply not safe.
OL,17,F"So if the owners and operators of
OL,18,Fthese dangerous facilities aren't
OL,19,Ftaking it upon themselves... then that
OL,20,Fis exactly why we have to legislate
OL,21,Ffor these changes."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
